Given an array of numbers, print all elements that are a power of 7.

Example
Input:  [1, 7, 49, 50, 343, 10]
Output: 7 49 343


let arr = [1, 7, 49, 50, 343, 10];

// Loop through each element of the array
for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {

    // Take the current array element
    let num = arr[i];

    // If the number is less than 7,
    // it cannot be a power of 7, so skip it
    if (num < 7) {
        continue; // move to the next element
    }

    // Keep dividing the number by 7
    // as long as it is perfectly divisible by 7
    while (num % 7 === 0) {
        num = num / 7; // reduce the number
    }

    // After removing all factors of 7,
    // if the number becomes 1,
    // then the original number was a power of 7
    if (num === 1) {
        console.log(arr[i]);  // print the original number
    }
}
Time Complexity: O(n log n) why 
Because we traverse the array once, and for each element we may divide it by 7 multiple times, which takes logarithmic time.
Space Complexity
O(1)
Only one extra variable (num) is used.
