Second Largest Element in an Array without sorting?
[3, 7, 2, 9, 5]
Output: 7
Explanation:
Largest = 9
Second Largest = 7

Solution:
let largest = -Infinity;
let secondLargest = -Infinity;

for (let i = 0; i < arr.length; i++) {
    if (arr[i] > largest) {
        secondLargest = largest;
        largest = arr[i];
    } 
    else if (arr[i] > secondLargest && arr[i] !== largest) {
        secondLargest = arr[i];
    }
}




Dry Run 
[5, 9, 9, 3]
And focus ONLY on this line:

else if (arr[i] > secondLargest && arr[i] !== largest)
üéØ Goal
Find:

 Largest
 Second Largest

‚úÖ Start
largest = -‚àû
secondLargest = -‚àû
üîπ Step 1 ‚Üí First number = 5
5 > -‚àû ‚úÖ
So:

largest = 5
secondLargest = -‚àû
üîπ Step 2 ‚Üí Next number = 9
9 > 5 ‚úÖ
So:

secondLargest = 5
largest = 9
Now:

largest = 9
secondLargest = 5
üîπ Step 3 ‚Üí Next number = 9 (duplicate!)
Check first if:

9 > 9 ‚ùå
Now comes your confusing part:

else if (arr[i] > secondLargest && arr[i] !== largest)
Let‚Äôs check slowly:

üëâ arr[i] > secondLargest ?
9 > 5 ‚úÖ
üëâ arr[i] !== largest ?
9 !== 9 ‚ùå
Because both are 9.

So:

TRUE && FALSE = FALSE
Nothing happens.

üëâ secondLargest stays 5.

‚ùì Why?
Because second largest CANNOT be same as largest.

üîπ Step 4 ‚Üí Next number = 3
Check:

3 > 9 ‚ùå
3 > 5 ‚ùå
Ignore.

‚úÖ Final Answer
largest = 9
secondLargest = 5
